<h4>
    Items with Color
</h4>
<p>
    In physics, we say there are six colors in the rainbow:
    red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and violet.
    These six colors exist because of
    <a href = '/pod/waves/the_electromagnetic_spectrum_quantitative/choosing_color_by_wavelength'>electromagnetic waves of different wavelengths</a>.
</p>

<ul class = 'principleList'>
    <li>
        When an electromagnetic wave of the <strong>same color</strong>
        strikes an object, it reflects that wave.
    </li>
    <li>
        When an electromagnetic wave of a <strong>different color</strong>
        strikes an object, it absorbs that wave.
    </li>
    <li>
        The reflected wave goes into your eye,
        telling your brain what color something is.
    </li>
</ul>


