<h4>
    Implications
</h4>

<ul class = 'principleList'>
    <li>
        When waring black clothing, you feel <emph>warmer</emph>,
        because your clothing absorbs all wavelengths
        of visible light.
    </li>
    <li>
        When wearing  white clothing, you feel <emph>cooler</emph>,
        because your clothing does not absorb any wavelengths
        of visible light.
    </li>
    <li>
        Lots of white objects can be extremely bright, sometimes to the point
        where they are uncomfortable to your eyes,
        because they reflect so much light.
    </li>
    <li>
        Having a very white surface,
        such as the polar ice caps,
        cools down a planet because it reflects more light from
        its star.
        This effect is called <a href = 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Albedo'>albedo</a>.
    </li>
</ul>

